acquire column names of a Hail Table

Source: R/colnames.R
colnames.hail.table.Table.Rd

acquire column names of a Hail Table

# S3 method for hail.table.Table
colnames(x, ...)

Arguments

x

instance of hail.table.Table

...

not used

Value

character()

Note

writes one line of table to disk to retrieve field names

Examples

hl = hail_init()
annopath <- path_1kg_annotations()
tab <- hl$import_table(annopath, impute=TRUE)$key_by("Sample")
colnames(tab)
#> [1] "Sample"              "Population"          "SuperPopulation"    
#> [4] "isFemale"            "PurpleHair"          "CaffeineConsumption"
